{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019sKrj7YbYM9poFgFY3C4Ls","type":"tool_result","content":"     1â†’# Cloche Usage\n     2â†’\n     3â†’Cloche runs containerized workflows for autonomous coding agents. You define a\n     4â†’workflow graph in the `.cloche` DSL, Cloche copies your project into a Docker\n     5â†’container, runs the workflow steps (agent prompts and shell scripts), and extracts\n     6â†’results to a git branch.\n     7â†’\n     8â†’## Core Concepts\n     9â†’\n    10â†’- **Workflow**: A directed graph of steps connected by named-result wiring.\n    11â†’- **Step**: A unit of work. Type is inferred: `prompt` = agent step, `run` = script step, `workflow_name` = workflow step (host only).\n    12â†’- **Result**: A named outcome reported by a step (e.g. `success`, `fail`, `needs-research`). Steps declare their possible results; the engine follows wiring based on the reported result.\n    13â†’- **Wiring**: Maps `step:result` pairs to the next step. Separate from step definitions.\n    14â†’- **Terminals**: `done` (success) and `abort` (failure) are built-in terminal targets.\n    15â†’\n    16â†’## Workflow DSL\n    17â†’\n    18â†’Workflow files use the `.cloche` extension and live in `.cloche/`. The first step\n    19â†’declared is the entry point. Graphs are validated at parse time (all results wired,\n    20â†’no orphans, entry point exists).\n    21â†’\n    22â†’### Minimal Example\n    23â†’\n    24â†’```\n    25â†’workflow \"develop\" {\n    26â†’  step implement {\n    27â†’    prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    28â†’    results = [success, fail]\n    29â†’  }\n    30â†’\n    31â†’  step test {\n    32â†’    run = \"make test 2>&1\"\n    33â†’    results = [success, fail]\n    34â†’  }\n    35â†’\n    36â†’  implement:success -> test\n    37â†’  implement:fail -> abort\n    38â†’  test:success -> done\n    39â†’  test:fail -> abort\n    40â†’}\n    41â†’```\n    42â†’\n    43â†’### Step Configuration\n    44â†’\n    45â†’| Key | Type | Description |\n    46â†’|-----|------|-------------|\n    47â†’| `prompt` | string or `file(\"path\")` | Prompt template. Makes this an agent step. |\n    48â†’| `run` | string | Shell command. Makes this a script step. |\n    49â†’| `workflow_name` | string | Container workflow to dispatch. Makes this a workflow step (host only). |\n    50â†’| `results` | ident list | Declared result names, e.g. `[success, fail, give-up]`. |\n    51â†’| `max_attempts` | string | Max retries before automatic `give-up` result, e.g. `\"2\"`. |\n    52â†’| `timeout` | string | Step timeout as Go duration, e.g. `\"30m\"`, `\"2h\"`. Default: 30m. |\n    53â†’| `agent_command` | string | Agent binary name(s), comma-separated for fallback chains, e.g. `\"claude,gemini\"`. |\n    54â†’| `agent_args` | string | Override default agent arguments. |\n    55â†’| `feedback` | string | Set to `\"true\"` to include `.cloche/output/*.log` content in the prompt. |\n    56â†’| `prompt_step` | string | For workflow steps: which preceding step's output to use as the prompt. |\n    57â†’\n    58â†’A step must have exactly one of `prompt`, `run`, or `workflow_name`.\n    59â†’\n    60â†’### The `file()` Function\n    61â†’\n    62â†’`file(\"path\")` reads the file at the given path relative to the working directory\n    63â†’(`/workspace/` in containers) at execution time, not parse time. Use it for prompt\n    64â†’templates:\n    65â†’\n    66â†’```\n    67â†’prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    68â†’```\n    69â†’\n    70â†’### The `container {}` Block\n    71â†’\n    72â†’Can appear at step level or workflow level. Keys are stored with a `container.` prefix.\n    73â†’\n    74â†’**Step level** â€” per-step container config:\n    75â†’```\n    76â†’step code {\n    77â†’  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    78â†’  container {\n    79â†’    image         = \"custom-agent:v2\"\n    80â†’    memory        = \"4g\"\n    81â†’    network_allow = [\"docs.python.org\", \"api.example.com\"]\n    82â†’  }\n    83â†’  results = [success, fail]\n    84â†’}\n    85â†’```\n    86â†’\n    87â†’**Workflow level** â€” defaults for all steps:\n    88â†’```\n    89â†’workflow \"develop\" {\n    90â†’  container {\n    91â†’    agent_command = \"gemini\"\n    92â†’    image         = \"myregistry/myimage:v2\"\n    93â†’    memory        = \"4g\"\n    94â†’  }\n    95â†’  ...\n    96â†’}\n    97â†’```\n    98â†’\n    99â†’Supported keys: `image`, `memory`, `network_allow`, `agent_command`, `agent_args`.\n   100â†’\n   101â†’### Wiring Syntax\n   102â†’\n   103â†’Connect steps with `step:result -> next_step`:\n   104â†’\n   105â†’```\n   106â†’implement:success -> test\n   107â†’implement:fail -> abort\n   108â†’test:success -> done\n   109â†’test:fail -> fix\n   110â†’```\n   111â†’\n   112â†’### Wire Output Mappings\n   113â†’\n   114â†’Extract values from a step's JSON output and inject as env vars into the target:\n   115â†’\n   116â†’```\n   117â†’step-a:success -> step-b [ ENV_VAR = output.field, OTHER = output.list[0].name ]\n   118â†’```\n   119â†’\n   120â†’Path expressions:\n   121â†’\n   122â†’| Expression | Meaning |\n   123â†’|---|---|\n   124â†’| `output` | Raw output (full string) |\n   125â†’| `output.key` | JSON object field access |\n   126â†’| `output[N]` | JSON array index (0-based) |\n   127â†’| `output.a.b.c` | Deeply nested field access |\n   128â†’| `output.items[0].name` | Mixed field and index chaining |\n   129â†’\n   130â†’If the output is valid JSON, path expressions navigate the structure. If it's plain\n   131â†’text, only bare `output` works.\n   132â†’\n   133â†’### Retry Loops\n   134â†’\n   135â†’Wire failures back to earlier steps:\n   136â†’\n   137â†’```\n   138â†’test:fail -> fix\n   139â†’fix:success -> test    // retry the test\n   140â†’fix:fail -> abort\n   141â†’```\n   142â†’\n   143â†’Use `max_attempts` to cap retries. When exhausted, the step returns `give-up`:\n   144â†’\n   145â†’```\n   146â†’step fix {\n   147â†’  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/fix.md\")\n   148â†’  max_attempts = \"2\"\n   149â†’  results = [success, fail, give-up]\n   150â†’}\n   151â†’```\n   152â†’\n   153â†’### Parallel Branches (Fanout)\n   154â†’\n   155â†’Wire one result to multiple targets for concurrent execution:\n   156â†’\n   157â†’```\n   158â†’test:success -> lint\n   159â†’test:success -> quality\n   160â†’```\n   161â†’\n   162â†’### Collect (Join)\n   163â†’\n   164â†’Synchronize parallel branches:\n   165â†’\n   166â†’```\n   167â†’collect all(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\n   168â†’collect any(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\n   169â†’```\n   170â†’\n   171â†’`all` fires when every condition is met. `any` fires when at least one is.\n   172â†’\n   173â†’### Comments\n   174â†’\n   175â†’Line comments with `//`:\n   176â†’\n   177â†’```\n   178â†’// This is a comment\n   179â†’implement:success -> test  // inline comment\n   180â†’```\n   181â†’\n   182â†’## Result Protocol\n   183â†’\n   184â†’Steps report results by printing a marker line to stdout:\n   185â†’\n   186â†’```\n   187â†’CLOCHE_RESULT:<name>\n   188â†’```\n   189â†’\n   190â†’For example: `CLOCHE_RESULT:success`, `CLOCHE_RESULT:needs-research`, `CLOCHE_RESULT:give-up`.\n   191â†’\n   192â†’Rules:\n   193â†’- The **last** `CLOCHE_RESULT:` line wins if multiple are printed.\n   194â†’- Marker lines are **stripped** from captured output (not passed to logs or downstream steps).\n   195â†’- The result name must match one of the step's declared `results`.\n   196â†’- For script steps with no marker: exit 0 = `success`, exit non-zero = `fail`.\n   197â†’- For agent steps: if exit non-zero with a marker, the marker result is used. If exit non-zero without a marker, falls back to the next agent in the fallback chain (or returns `fail` if last).\n   198â†’\n   199â†’## Prompt Assembly\n   200â†’\n   201â†’When an agent step runs, Cloche assembles a prompt from these sections (joined by blank lines):\n   202â†’\n   203â†’1. **Step template**: The step's `prompt` content (inline string or resolved `file(\"path\")`).\n   204â†’2. **User request**: Content of `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt` (set via `--prompt` flag), prefixed with `## User Request`.\n   205â†’3. **Validation output** (opt-in): If `feedback = \"true\"`, reads all `.log` files from `.cloche/output/` and includes them prefixed with `## Validation Output`.\n   206â†’4. **Result selection**: Lists the step's declared results with instructions to print exactly one `CLOCHE_RESULT:<name>` marker.\n   207â†’\n   208â†’The assembled prompt is passed to the agent command via stdin.\n   209â†’\n   210â†’## Agent Command Resolution\n   211â†’\n   212â†’Priority (highest to lowest):\n   213â†’1. Step-level `agent_command`\n   214â†’2. Workflow-level `container { agent_command }`\n   215â†’3. `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND` environment variable\n   216â†’4. Default: `claude`\n   217â†’\n   218â†’### Fallback Chains\n   219â†’\n   220â†’Comma-separated commands are tried in order:\n   221â†’\n   222â†’```\n   223â†’agent_command = \"claude,gemini,codex\"\n   224â†’```\n   225â†’\n   226â†’- **Command not found / failed to start** â€” try next command\n   227â†’- **Exit non-zero without `CLOCHE_RESULT` marker** â€” try next command\n   228â†’- **Exit non-zero with `CLOCHE_RESULT` marker** â€” use that result (no fallback)\n   229â†’- **Exit 0** â€” use result (no fallback)\n   230â†’- **All commands fail to start** â€” step returns an error\n   231â†’- **Last command crashes without marker** â€” step returns `fail`\n   232â†’\n   233â†’Known agents (e.g. `claude`) get default arguments (`-p --output-format stream-json --verbose --dangerously-skip-permissions`). Unknown agents receive the prompt on stdin with no flags. Override with `agent_args`.\n   234â†’\n   235â†’## Workflow Locations\n   236â†’\n   237â†’**Container workflows** (`.cloche/*.cloche` except `host.cloche`) run inside Docker\n   238â†’via `cloche-agent`. Steps may only be `agent` or `script` type.\n   239â†’\n   240â†’**Host workflow** (`.cloche/host.cloche`) runs on the host machine as the daemon.\n   241â†’Steps may be `agent`, `script`, or `workflow` type. The `workflow_name` step type\n   242â†’dispatches a container workflow run and blocks until it completes.\n   243â†’\n   244â†’### Host Workflow Example\n   245â†’\n   246â†’```\n   247â†’workflow \"main\" {\n   248â†’  step ready-tasks {\n   249â†’    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/ready-tasks.sh 1\"\n   250â†’    results = [success, fail]\n   251â†’  }\n   252â†’\n   253â†’  step prepare-prompt {\n   254â†’    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh\"\n   255â†’    results = [success, fail]\n   256â†’  }\n   257â†’\n   258â†’  step develop {\n   259â†’    workflow_name = \"develop\"\n   260â†’    results       = [success, fail]\n   261â†’  }\n   262â†’\n   263â†’  ready-tasks:success -> prepare-prompt [\n   264â†’    CLOCHE_TASK_ID    = output[0].id,\n   265â†’    CLOCHE_TASK_TITLE = output[0].title,\n   266â†’    CLOCHE_TASK_BODY  = output[0].description\n   267â†’  ]\n   268â†’  ready-tasks:fail       -> abort\n   269â†’  prepare-prompt:success -> develop [ CLOCHE_TASK_ID = output.task_id ]\n   270â†’  prepare-prompt:fail    -> abort\n   271â†’  develop:success        -> done\n   272â†’  develop:fail           -> done\n   273â†’}\n   274â†’```\n   275â†’\n   276â†’### Host Step Environment Variables\n   277â†’\n   278â†’| Variable | Description |\n   279â†’|----------|-------------|\n   280â†’| `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` | Absolute path to the project directory on the host. |\n   281â†’| `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT` | Path where this step should write its output (for output mappings). |\n   282â†’| `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT` | Path to the output file from the immediately preceding step. |\n   283â†’| Wire-mapped vars | Any env vars declared in wire output mappings (e.g. `CLOCHE_TASK_ID`). |\n   284â†’\n   285â†’### Container Environment Variables\n   286â†’\n   287â†’| Variable | Description |\n   288â†’|----------|-------------|\n   289â†’| `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` | The run ID for this workflow execution. |\n   290â†’| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | Passed through from the host if set. |\n   291â†’| `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND` | Overrides the default agent command inside the container. |\n   292â†’\n   293â†’## Complete Example: Container Workflow with Parallel Validation\n   294â†’\n   295â†’```\n   296â†’workflow \"develop\" {\n   297â†’  step implement {\n   298â†’    prompt = file(\"prompts/implement.md\")\n   299â†’    results = [success, fail]\n   300â†’  }\n   301â†’\n   302â†’  step test {\n   303â†’    run = \"bundle exec rake test 2>&1\"\n   304â†’    results = [success, fail]\n   305â†’  }\n   306â†’\n   307â†’  step lint {\n   308â†’    run = \"bundle exec rubocop 2>&1\"\n   309â†’    results = [success, fail]\n   310â†’  }\n   311â†’\n   312â†’  step quality {\n   313â†’    run = \"python3 scripts/quality-check.py 2>&1\"\n   314â†’    results = [success, fail]\n   315â†’  }\n   316â†’\n   317â†’  step fix {\n   318â†’    prompt = file(\"prompts/fix.md\")\n   319â†’    max_attempts = \"2\"\n   320â†’    results = [success, fail, give-up]\n   321â†’  }\n   322â†’\n   323â†’  implement:success -> test\n   324â†’  implement:fail -> abort\n   325â†’\n   326â†’  test:success -> lint\n   327â†’  test:success -> quality\n   328â†’  test:fail -> fix\n   329â†’\n   330â†’  lint:fail -> fix\n   331â†’  quality:fail -> fix\n   332â†’  collect all(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\n   333â†’\n   334â†’  fix:success -> test\n   335â†’  fix:fail -> abort\n   336â†’  fix:give-up -> abort\n   337â†’}\n   338â†’```\n   339â†’\n   340â†’## Container Isolation Model\n   341â†’\n   342â†’- **Files in**: `docker cp` copies the project into `/workspace/`. No bind mounts. Override files from `.cloche/overrides/` are applied on top. `.git/` is included.\n   343â†’- **Files out**: On completion, the daemon extracts results via `docker cp` into a git worktree and commits to a `cloche/<run-id>` branch.\n   344â†’- **Auth mounts**: `~/.claude` and `~/.claude.json` are bind-mounted read-only for Claude Code session reuse.\n   345â†’- **Network**: Containers have network access (needed for API calls).\n   346â†’- **Cleanup**: Containers are removed after successful runs unless `--keep-container` is set. Failed runs always keep their container.\n   347â†’\n   348â†’Your project directory is never modified by the container.\n   349â†’\n   350â†’## CLI Reference\n   351â†’\n   352â†’### `cloche init`\n   353â†’\n   354â†’Scaffold a new Cloche project.\n   355â†’\n   356â†’```\n   357â†’cloche init [--workflow <name>] [--base-image <base>]\n   358â†’```\n   359â†’\n   360â†’| Flag | Default | Description |\n   361â†’|------|---------|-------------|\n   362â†’| `--workflow <name>` | `develop` | Workflow name. Creates `.cloche/<name>.cloche`. |\n   363â†’| `--base-image <base>` | `cloche-base:latest` | Base Docker image for the generated Dockerfile. |\n   364â†’\n   365â†’Creates `.cloche/` with workflow file, Dockerfile, `config.toml`, prompt templates,\n   366â†’host workflow (`host.cloche`), and prompt generation script. Skips existing files.\n   367â†’\n   368â†’### `cloche run`\n   369â†’\n   370â†’Launch a workflow run.\n   371â†’\n   372â†’```\n   373â†’cloche run --workflow <name> [--prompt \"...\"] [--title \"...\"] [--keep-container]\n   374â†’```\n   375â†’\n   376â†’| Flag | Description |\n   377â†’|------|-------------|\n   378â†’| `--workflow <name>` | Workflow name. Resolves to `.cloche/<name>.cloche`. |\n   379â†’| `--prompt \"...\"`, `-p` | Inline prompt written to `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt`. |\n   380â†’| `--title \"...\"` | One-line summary for status display. Auto-generated if omitted. |\n   381â†’| `--keep-container` | Keep container on success (failed runs always keep it). |\n   382â†’\n   383â†’Must be run from inside a git repository. The daemon auto-rebuilds the Docker image\n   384â†’when `.cloche/Dockerfile` changes.\n   385â†’\n   386â†’### `cloche status`\n   387â†’\n   388â†’```\n   389â†’cloche status <run-id>\n   390â†’```\n   391â†’\n   392â†’Shows run title, type (`host`/`container`), state, active steps, and per-step results.\n   393â†’\n   394â†’### `cloche list`\n   395â†’\n   396â†’```\n   397â†’cloche list [--all]\n   398â†’```\n   399â†’\n   400â†’Lists runs from the last hour (or all with `--all`).\n   401â†’\n   402â†’### `cloche logs`\n   403â†’\n   404â†’```\n   405â†’cloche logs <run-id> [--step <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [--follow]\n   406â†’```\n   407â†’\n   408â†’| Flag | Description |\n   409â†’|------|-------------|\n   410â†’| `--step <name>` | Show only logs for the specified step. |\n   411â†’| `--type <full\\|script\\|llm>` | Log type filter. |\n   412â†’| `--follow`, `-f` | Stream live logs via SSE with color-coded output (requires `CLOCHE_HTTP`). |\n   413â†’\n   414â†’For active runs, `cloche logs <run-id>` streams LLM output and step status in real time via gRPC (no `--follow` needed). For completed runs, it serves the saved log files.\n   415â†’\n   416â†’### `cloche poll`\n   417â†’\n   418â†’```\n   419â†’cloche poll <run-id>\n   420â†’```\n   421â†’\n   422â†’Block until the run finishes. Polls every 2 seconds. Exits 0 on success, 1 on failure.\n   423â†’\n   424â†’### `cloche stop`\n   425â†’\n   426â†’```\n   427â†’cloche stop <run-id>\n   428â†’```\n   429â†’\n   430â†’### `cloche delete`\n   431â†’\n   432â†’```\n   433â†’cloche delete <container-or-run-id>\n   434â†’```\n   435â†’\n   436â†’Delete a retained Docker container by container ID or run ID.\n   437â†’\n   438â†’### `cloche health`\n   439â†’\n   440â†’```\n   441â†’cloche health\n   442â†’```\n   443â†’\n   444â†’Show per-project pass/fail summary. Requires `CLOCHE_HTTP`.\n   445â†’\n   446â†’### `cloche shutdown`\n   447â†’\n   448â†’```\n   449â†’cloche shutdown\n   450â†’```\n   451â†’\n   452â†’## Project Layout\n   453â†’\n   454â†’```\n   455â†’my-project/\n   456â†’â”śâ”€â”€ .cloche/\n   457â†’â”‚   â”śâ”€â”€ develop.cloche        # Container workflow\n   458â†’â”‚   â”śâ”€â”€ host.cloche           # Host orchestration workflow\n   459â†’â”‚   â”śâ”€â”€ Dockerfile            # Container image definition\n   460â†’â”‚   â”śâ”€â”€ config.toml           # Project configuration\n   461â†’â”‚   â”śâ”€â”€ prompts/              # Prompt templates\n   462â†’â”‚   â”‚   â”śâ”€â”€ implement.md\n   463â†’â”‚   â”‚   â”śâ”€â”€ fix.md\n   464â†’â”‚   â”‚   â””â”€â”€ update-docs.md\n   465â†’â”‚   â”śâ”€â”€ scripts/              # Host-side scripts\n   466â†’â”‚   â”śâ”€â”€ overrides/            # Files copied on top of /workspace/\n   467â†’â”‚   â”‚   â””â”€â”€ CLAUDE.md         # Container-specific CLAUDE.md (optional)\n   468â†’â”‚   â””â”€â”€ <run-id>/             # Runtime state (gitignored)\n   469â†’â”‚       â”śâ”€â”€ prompt.txt        # User prompt\n   470â†’â”‚       â”śâ”€â”€ output/\n   471â†’â”‚       â”‚   â”śâ”€â”€ full.log      # Unified log\n   472â†’â”‚       â”‚   â”śâ”€â”€ test.log      # Per-step script output\n   473â†’â”‚       â”‚   â””â”€â”€ llm-impl.log  # Per-step LLM conversation\n   474â†’â”‚       â”śâ”€â”€ attempt_count/    # Retry counters for max_attempts\n   475â†’â”‚       â””â”€â”€ history.log       # Step execution log\n   476â†’â”śâ”€â”€ src/                      # Project source (untouched by Cloche)\n   477â†’â””â”€â”€ .git/\n   478â†’```\n   479â†’\n   480â†’## Daemon Configuration\n   481â†’\n   482â†’| Variable | Default | Description |\n   483â†’|----------|---------|-------------|\n   484â†’| `CLOCHE_LISTEN` | `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock` | Listen address |\n   485â†’| `CLOCHE_DB` | `cloche.db` | SQLite database path |\n   486â†’| `CLOCHE_RUNTIME` | `docker` | `docker` or `local` (subprocess, for dev only) |\n   487â†’| `CLOCHE_IMAGE` | `cloche-agent:latest` | Default Docker image |\n   488â†’| `CLOCHE_HTTP` | _(unset)_ | HTTP address for web dashboard. Not started unless set. |\n   489â†’| `CLOCHE_AGENT_PATH` | _(auto)_ | Path to `cloche-agent` binary (local runtime) |\n   490â†’| `CLOCHE_LLM_COMMAND` | _(unset)_ | Command for LLM calls (evolution, merge conflicts) |\n   491â†’| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | _(unset)_ | Passed into Docker containers |\n   492â†’| `CLOCHE_EXTRA_MOUNTS` | _(unset)_ | Extra bind mounts (comma-separated `host:container`) |\n   493â†’| `CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV` | _(unset)_ | Extra env vars (comma-separated `KEY=VALUE`) |\n   494â†’\n   495â†’### Client Configuration\n   496â†’\n   497â†’| Variable | Default | Description |\n   498â†’|----------|---------|-------------|\n   499â†’| `CLOCHE_ADDR` | `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock` | Daemon gRPC address |\n   500â†’| `CLOCHE_HTTP` | `localhost:8080` | Daemon HTTP address |\n   501â†’\n   502â†’## Dockerfile Requirements\n   503â†’\n   504â†’The container image must have:\n   505â†’- `cloche-agent` binary at `/usr/local/bin/cloche-agent`\n   506â†’- `git` installed\n   507â†’- An `agent` user (cloche wraps commands with `chown` + `su agent`)\n   508â†’- `/workspace` as the working directory\n   509â†’- Your project's build dependencies and the agent binary (e.g. `claude`)\n   510â†’\n   511â†’## Build Commands\n   512â†’\n   513â†’```\n   514â†’make build          # Build all binaries to bin/\n   515â†’make test           # Run all tests\n   516â†’make test-short     # Run tests (skip slow ones)\n   517â†’make lint           # Run go vet\n   518â†’make proto          # Regenerate gRPC code from protobuf\n   519â†’make docker-build   # Build the cloche-agent Docker image\n   520â†’make install        # Build, install to ~/.local/bin/, restart daemon\n   521â†’make clean          # Remove bin/\n   522â†’```\n   523â†’"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9e26bca6-f7d7-4725-aa23-0ce35c36d238","uuid":"7d976991-45e6-4fc4-8557-6206bb30247e","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/USAGE.md","content":"# Cloche Usage\n\nCloche runs containerized workflows for autonomous coding agents. You define a\nworkflow graph in the `.cloche` DSL, Cloche copies your project into a Docker\ncontainer, runs the workflow steps (agent prompts and shell scripts), and extracts\nresults to a git branch.\n\n## Core Concepts\n\n- **Workflow**: A directed graph of steps connected by named-result wiring.\n- **Step**: A unit of work. Type is inferred: `prompt` = agent step, `run` = script step, `workflow_name` = workflow step (host only).\n- **Result**: A named outcome reported by a step (e.g. `success`, `fail`, `needs-research`). Steps declare their possible results; the engine follows wiring based on the reported result.\n- **Wiring**: Maps `step:result` pairs to the next step. Separate from step definitions.\n- **Terminals**: `done` (success) and `abort` (failure) are built-in terminal targets.\n\n## Workflow DSL\n\nWorkflow files use the `.cloche` extension and live in `.cloche/`. The first step\ndeclared is the entry point. Graphs are validated at parse time (all results wired,\nno orphans, entry point exists).\n\n### Minimal Example\n\n```\nworkflow \"develop\" {\n  step implement {\n    prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step test {\n    run = \"make test 2>&1\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  implement:success -> test\n  implement:fail -> abort\n  test:success -> done\n  test:fail -> abort\n}\n```\n\n### Step Configuration\n\n| Key | Type | Description |\n|-----|------|-------------|\n| `prompt` | string or `file(\"path\")` | Prompt template. Makes this an agent step. |\n| `run` | string | Shell command. Makes this a script step. |\n| `workflow_name` | string | Container workflow to dispatch. Makes this a workflow step (host only). |\n| `results` | ident list | Declared result names, e.g. `[success, fail, give-up]`. |\n| `max_attempts` | string | Max retries before automatic `give-up` result, e.g. `\"2\"`. |\n| `timeout` | string | Step timeout as Go duration, e.g. `\"30m\"`, `\"2h\"`. Default: 30m. |\n| `agent_command` | string | Agent binary name(s), comma-separated for fallback chains, e.g. `\"claude,gemini\"`. |\n| `agent_args` | string | Override default agent arguments. |\n| `feedback` | string | Set to `\"true\"` to include `.cloche/output/*.log` content in the prompt. |\n| `prompt_step` | string | For workflow steps: which preceding step's output to use as the prompt. |\n\nA step must have exactly one of `prompt`, `run`, or `workflow_name`.\n\n### The `file()` Function\n\n`file(\"path\")` reads the file at the given path relative to the working directory\n(`/workspace/` in containers) at execution time, not parse time. Use it for prompt\ntemplates:\n\n```\nprompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n```\n\n### The `container {}` Block\n\nCan appear at step level or workflow level. Keys are stored with a `container.` prefix.\n\n**Step level** â€” per-step container config:\n```\nstep code {\n  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n  container {\n    image         = \"custom-agent:v2\"\n    memory        = \"4g\"\n    network_allow = [\"docs.python.org\", \"api.example.com\"]\n  }\n  results = [success, fail]\n}\n```\n\n**Workflow level** â€” defaults for all steps:\n```\nworkflow \"develop\" {\n  container {\n    agent_command = \"gemini\"\n    image         = \"myregistry/myimage:v2\"\n    memory        = \"4g\"\n  }\n  ...\n}\n```\n\nSupported keys: `image`, `memory`, `network_allow`, `agent_command`, `agent_args`.\n\n### Wiring Syntax\n\nConnect steps with `step:result -> next_step`:\n\n```\nimplement:success -> test\nimplement:fail -> abort\ntest:success -> done\ntest:fail -> fix\n```\n\n### Wire Output Mappings\n\nExtract values from a step's JSON output and inject as env vars into the target:\n\n```\nstep-a:success -> step-b [ ENV_VAR = output.field, OTHER = output.list[0].name ]\n```\n\nPath expressions:\n\n| Expression | Meaning |\n|---|---|\n| `output` | Raw output (full string) |\n| `output.key` | JSON object field access |\n| `output[N]` | JSON array index (0-based) |\n| `output.a.b.c` | Deeply nested field access |\n| `output.items[0].name` | Mixed field and index chaining |\n\nIf the output is valid JSON, path expressions navigate the structure. If it's plain\ntext, only bare `output` works.\n\n### Retry Loops\n\nWire failures back to earlier steps:\n\n```\ntest:fail -> fix\nfix:success -> test    // retry the test\nfix:fail -> abort\n```\n\nUse `max_attempts` to cap retries. When exhausted, the step returns `give-up`:\n\n```\nstep fix {\n  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/fix.md\")\n  max_attempts = \"2\"\n  results = [success, fail, give-up]\n}\n```\n\n### Parallel Branches (Fanout)\n\nWire one result to multiple targets for concurrent execution:\n\n```\ntest:success -> lint\ntest:success -> quality\n```\n\n### Collect (Join)\n\nSynchronize parallel branches:\n\n```\ncollect all(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\ncollect any(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\n```\n\n`all` fires when every condition is met. `any` fires when at least one is.\n\n### Comments\n\nLine comments with `//`:\n\n```\n// This is a comment\nimplement:success -> test  // inline comment\n```\n\n## Result Protocol\n\nSteps report results by printing a marker line to stdout:\n\n```\nCLOCHE_RESULT:<name>\n```\n\nFor example: `CLOCHE_RESULT:success`, `CLOCHE_RESULT:needs-research`, `CLOCHE_RESULT:give-up`.\n\nRules:\n- The **last** `CLOCHE_RESULT:` line wins if multiple are printed.\n- Marker lines are **stripped** from captured output (not passed to logs or downstream steps).\n- The result name must match one of the step's declared `results`.\n- For script steps with no marker: exit 0 = `success`, exit non-zero = `fail`.\n- For agent steps: if exit non-zero with a marker, the marker result is used. If exit non-zero without a marker, falls back to the next agent in the fallback chain (or returns `fail` if last).\n\n## Prompt Assembly\n\nWhen an agent step runs, Cloche assembles a prompt from these sections (joined by blank lines):\n\n1. **Step template**: The step's `prompt` content (inline string or resolved `file(\"path\")`).\n2. **User request**: Content of `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt` (set via `--prompt` flag), prefixed with `## User Request`.\n3. **Validation output** (opt-in): If `feedback = \"true\"`, reads all `.log` files from `.cloche/output/` and includes them prefixed with `## Validation Output`.\n4. **Result selection**: Lists the step's declared results with instructions to print exactly one `CLOCHE_RESULT:<name>` marker.\n\nThe assembled prompt is passed to the agent command via stdin.\n\n## Agent Command Resolution\n\nPriority (highest to lowest):\n1. Step-level `agent_command`\n2. Workflow-level `container { agent_command }`\n3. `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND` environment variable\n4. Default: `claude`\n\n### Fallback Chains\n\nComma-separated commands are tried in order:\n\n```\nagent_command = \"claude,gemini,codex\"\n```\n\n- **Command not found / failed to start** â€” try next command\n- **Exit non-zero without `CLOCHE_RESULT` marker** â€” try next command\n- **Exit non-zero with `CLOCHE_RESULT` marker** â€” use that result (no fallback)\n- **Exit 0** â€” use result (no fallback)\n- **All commands fail to start** â€” step returns an error\n- **Last command crashes without marker** â€” step returns `fail`\n\nKnown agents (e.g. `claude`) get default arguments (`-p --output-format stream-json --verbose --dangerously-skip-permissions`). Unknown agents receive the prompt on stdin with no flags. Override with `agent_args`.\n\n## Workflow Locations\n\n**Container workflows** (`.cloche/*.cloche` except `host.cloche`) run inside Docker\nvia `cloche-agent`. Steps may only be `agent` or `script` type.\n\n**Host workflow** (`.cloche/host.cloche`) runs on the host machine as the daemon.\nSteps may be `agent`, `script`, or `workflow` type. The `workflow_name` step type\ndispatches a container workflow run and blocks until it completes.\n\n### Host Workflow Example\n\n```\nworkflow \"main\" {\n  step ready-tasks {\n    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/ready-tasks.sh 1\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step prepare-prompt {\n    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step develop {\n    workflow_name = \"develop\"\n    results       = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  ready-tasks:success -> prepare-prompt [\n    CLOCHE_TASK_ID    = output[0].id,\n    CLOCHE_TASK_TITLE = output[0].title,\n    CLOCHE_TASK_BODY  = output[0].description\n  ]\n  ready-tasks:fail       -> abort\n  prepare-prompt:success -> develop [ CLOCHE_TASK_ID = output.task_id ]\n  prepare-prompt:fail    -> abort\n  develop:success        -> done\n  develop:fail           -> done\n}\n```\n\n### Host Step Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Description |\n|----------|-------------|\n| `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` | Absolute path to the project directory on the host. |\n| `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT` | Path where this step should write its output (for output mappings). |\n| `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT` | Path to the output file from the immediately preceding step. |\n| Wire-mapped vars | Any env vars declared in wire output mappings (e.g. `CLOCHE_TASK_ID`). |\n\n### Container Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Description |\n|----------|-------------|\n| `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` | The run ID for this workflow execution. |\n| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | Passed through from the host if set. |\n| `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND` | Overrides the default agent command inside the container. |\n\n## Complete Example: Container Workflow with Parallel Validation\n\n```\nworkflow \"develop\" {\n  step implement {\n    prompt = file(\"prompts/implement.md\")\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step test {\n    run = \"bundle exec rake test 2>&1\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step lint {\n    run = \"bundle exec rubocop 2>&1\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step quality {\n    run = \"python3 scripts/quality-check.py 2>&1\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step fix {\n    prompt = file(\"prompts/fix.md\")\n    max_attempts = \"2\"\n    results = [success, fail, give-up]\n  }\n\n  implement:success -> test\n  implement:fail -> abort\n\n  test:success -> lint\n  test:success -> quality\n  test:fail -> fix\n\n  lint:fail -> fix\n  quality:fail -> fix\n  collect all(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\n\n  fix:success -> test\n  fix:fail -> abort\n  fix:give-up -> abort\n}\n```\n\n## Container Isolation Model\n\n- **Files in**: `docker cp` copies the project into `/workspace/`. No bind mounts. Override files from `.cloche/overrides/` are applied on top. `.git/` is included.\n- **Files out**: On completion, the daemon extracts results via `docker cp` into a git worktree and commits to a `cloche/<run-id>` branch.\n- **Auth mounts**: `~/.claude` and `~/.claude.json` are bind-mounted read-only for Claude Code session reuse.\n- **Network**: Containers have network access (needed for API calls).\n- **Cleanup**: Containers are removed after successful runs unless `--keep-container` is set. Failed runs always keep their container.\n\nYour project directory is never modified by the container.\n\n## CLI Reference\n\n### `cloche init`\n\nScaffold a new Cloche project.\n\n```\ncloche init [--workflow <name>] [--base-image <base>]\n```\n\n| Flag | Default | Description |\n|------|---------|-------------|\n| `--workflow <name>` | `develop` | Workflow name. Creates `.cloche/<name>.cloche`. |\n| `--base-image <base>` | `cloche-base:latest` | Base Docker image for the generated Dockerfile. |\n\nCreates `.cloche/` with workflow file, Dockerfile, `config.toml`, prompt templates,\nhost workflow (`host.cloche`), and prompt generation script. Skips existing files.\n\n### `cloche run`\n\nLaunch a workflow run.\n\n```\ncloche run --workflow <name> [--prompt \"...\"] [--title \"...\"] [--keep-container]\n```\n\n| Flag | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `--workflow <name>` | Workflow name. Resolves to `.cloche/<name>.cloche`. |\n| `--prompt \"...\"`, `-p` | Inline prompt written to `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt`. |\n| `--title \"...\"` | One-line summary for status display. Auto-generated if omitted. |\n| `--keep-container` | Keep container on success (failed runs always keep it). |\n\nMust be run from inside a git repository. The daemon auto-rebuilds the Docker image\nwhen `.cloche/Dockerfile` changes.\n\n### `cloche status`\n\n```\ncloche status <run-id>\n```\n\nShows run title, type (`host`/`container`), state, active steps, and per-step results.\n\n### `cloche list`\n\n```\ncloche list [--all]\n```\n\nLists runs from the last hour (or all with `--all`).\n\n### `cloche logs`\n\n```\ncloche logs <run-id> [--step <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [--follow]\n```\n\n| Flag | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `--step <name>` | Show only logs for the specified step. |\n| `--type <full\\|script\\|llm>` | Log type filter. |\n| `--follow`, `-f` | Stream live logs via SSE with color-coded output (requires `CLOCHE_HTTP`). |\n\nFor active runs, `cloche logs <run-id>` streams LLM output and step status in real time via gRPC (no `--follow` needed). For completed runs, it serves the saved log files.\n\n### `cloche poll`\n\n```\ncloche poll <run-id>\n```\n\nBlock until the run finishes. Polls every 2 seconds. Exits 0 on success, 1 on failure.\n\n### `cloche stop`\n\n```\ncloche stop <run-id>\n```\n\n### `cloche delete`\n\n```\ncloche delete <container-or-run-id>\n```\n\nDelete a retained Docker container by container ID or run ID.\n\n### `cloche health`\n\n```\ncloche health\n```\n\nShow per-project pass/fail summary. Requires `CLOCHE_HTTP`.\n\n### `cloche shutdown`\n\n```\ncloche shutdown\n```\n\n## Project Layout\n\n```\nmy-project/\nâ”śâ”€â”€ .cloche/\nâ”‚   â”śâ”€â”€ develop.cloche        # Container workflow\nâ”‚   â”śâ”€â”€ host.cloche           # Host orchestration workflow\nâ”‚   â”śâ”€â”€ Dockerfile            # Container image definition\nâ”‚   â”śâ”€â”€ config.toml           # Project configuration\nâ”‚   â”śâ”€â”€ prompts/              # Prompt templates\nâ”‚   â”‚   â”śâ”€â”€ implement.md\nâ”‚   â”‚   â”śâ”€â”€ fix.md\nâ”‚   â”‚   â””â”€â”€ update-docs.md\nâ”‚   â”śâ”€â”€ scripts/              # Host-side scripts\nâ”‚   â”śâ”€â”€ overrides/            # Files copied on top of /workspace/\nâ”‚   â”‚   â””â”€â”€ CLAUDE.md         # Container-specific CLAUDE.md (optional)\nâ”‚   â””â”€â”€ <run-id>/             # Runtime state (gitignored)\nâ”‚       â”śâ”€â”€ prompt.txt        # User prompt\nâ”‚       â”śâ”€â”€ output/\nâ”‚       â”‚   â”śâ”€â”€ full.log      # Unified log\nâ”‚       â”‚   â”śâ”€â”€ test.log      # Per-step script output\nâ”‚       â”‚   â””â”€â”€ llm-impl.log  # Per-step LLM conversation\nâ”‚       â”śâ”€â”€ attempt_count/    # Retry counters for max_attempts\nâ”‚       â””â”€â”€ history.log       # Step execution log\nâ”śâ”€â”€ src/                      # Project source (untouched by Cloche)\nâ””â”€â”€ .git/\n```\n\n## Daemon Configuration\n\n| Variable | Default | Description |\n|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `CLOCHE_LISTEN` | `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock` | Listen address |\n| `CLOCHE_DB` | `cloche.db` | SQLite database path |\n| `CLOCHE_RUNTIME` | `docker` | `docker` or `local` (subprocess, for dev only) |\n| `CLOCHE_IMAGE` | `cloche-agent:latest` | Default Docker image |\n| `CLOCHE_HTTP` | _(unset)_ | HTTP address for web dashboard. Not started unless set. |\n| `CLOCHE_AGENT_PATH` | _(auto)_ | Path to `cloche-agent` binary (local runtime) |\n| `CLOCHE_LLM_COMMAND` | _(unset)_ | Command for LLM calls (evolution, merge conflicts) |\n| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | _(unset)_ | Passed into Docker containers |\n| `CLOCHE_EXTRA_MOUNTS` | _(unset)_ | Extra bind mounts (comma-separated `host:container`) |\n| `CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV` | _(unset)_ | Extra env vars (comma-separated `KEY=VALUE`) |\n\n### Client Configuration\n\n| Variable | Default | Description |\n|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `CLOCHE_ADDR` | `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock` | Daemon gRPC address |\n| `CLOCHE_HTTP` | `localhost:8080` | Daemon HTTP address |\n\n## Dockerfile Requirements\n\nThe container image must have:\n- `cloche-agent` binary at `/usr/local/bin/cloche-agent`\n- `git` installed\n- An `agent` user (cloche wraps commands with `chown` + `su agent`)\n- `/workspace` as the working directory\n- Your project's build dependencies and the agent binary (e.g. `claude`)\n\n## Build Commands\n\n```\nmake build          # Build all binaries to bin/\nmake test           # Run all tests\nmake test-short     # Run tests (skip slow ones)\nmake lint           # Run go vet\nmake proto          # Regenerate gRPC code from protobuf\nmake docker-build   # Build the cloche-agent Docker image\nmake install        # Build, install to ~/.local/bin/, restart daemon\nmake clean          # Remove bin/\n```\n","numLines":523,"startLine":1,"totalLines":523}}}
